00:48:34,360 --> 00:48:35,760
I'm dazzled.

1033
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:39,040
You are beautiful and inspiring.

1034
00:48:39,440 --> 00:48:43,160
We don't know where you came
from.
You were an apparition.

1035
00:48:43,160 --> 00:48:46,880
You opened the Rusical
and really set the tone.

1036
00:48:46,880 --> 00:48:50,200
That lip-sync was quite long
and complicated,

1037
00:48:50,200 --> 00:48:51,720
it had different rhythms,

1038
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:55,560
but your delivery was truly
extraordinary.

1039
00:48:55,560 --> 00:48:58,080
It was a mix of Rika Zaraï and
Régine,

1040
00:48:58,080 --> 00:49:00,840
who are my idols, so I loved it,

1041
00:49:00,840 --> 00:49:02,720
and I want to see more of that.

1042
00:49:02,720 --> 00:49:04,440
Compliments feel good, right?

1043
00:49:04,440 --> 00:49:06,920
Yes, really good.

1044
00:49:06,920 --> 00:49:11,160
I'm in heaven now, thank you
very much.

1045
00:49:11,160 --> 00:49:13,400
[suspenseful sound]

1046
00:49:13,400 --> 00:49:14,880
Sara Forever!

1047
00:49:15,280 --> 00:49:16,880
Your performance in the Rusical

1048
00:49:17,120 --> 00:49:21,160
complemented Punani's perfectly.

1049
00:49:21,160 --> 00:49:23,320
Yes, your duet was perfect.

1050
00:49:23,320 --> 00:49:25,360
We really wanted to be your
girlfriends,

1051
00:49:25,360 --> 00:49:28,000
despite the fact that you
dislike people.

1052
00:49:29,360 --> 00:49:30,440
I tolerate them.

1053
00:49:30,760 --> 00:49:33,520
Yeah, it's kind of mutual.

1054
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:35,560
Your performance was great,

1055
00:49:35,560 --> 00:49:37,360
and I'm glad I discovered you.

1056
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:38,400
Thanks.

1057
00:49:38,400 --> 00:49:41,400
For Excess Couture,
I really like this camp look.

1058
00:49:41,400 --> 00:49:43,680
It's very pop.

1059
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:46,760
It's really funny, and at the
same time,

1060
00:49:46,760 --> 00:49:50,800
you totally fulfilled
the excessiveness of the theme.

1061
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:53,840
It's funny, but I would have
liked to see you

1062
00:49:54,160 --> 00:49:56,000
in a haute couture outfit.

1063
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:58,920
[suspenseful sound]

1064
00:49:58,920 --> 00:50:01,200
-Keiona!
-Hey!

1065
00:50:02,040 --> 00:50:06,960
I love this look,
because I understand all the
references.

1066
00:50:06,960 --> 00:50:10,520
Once again, you're paying
tribute
to our ballroom culture.

1067
00:50:10,760 --> 00:50:14,760
You're doing it with elegance,
and I'm delighted.

1068
00:50:14,760 --> 00:50:19,600
When I saw you as Quasimollo,
I immediately thought of Lucas.

1069
00:50:20,280 --> 00:50:23,280
This young boy who was bullied
at school

1070
00:50:23,880 --> 00:50:26,440
and committed suicide at home.

1071
00:50:26,440 --> 00:50:28,960
What you did tonight could save

1072
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:31,160
the lives of many of these young
people.

1073
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:34,320
It's not just a queen
who told the story of
Quasimollo.

1074
00:50:34,320 --> 00:50:37,320
It's a queen who told the story
of an entire community.

1075
00:50:37,320 --> 00:50:39,680
And that really touched me,
because I expected to laugh

1076
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:41,480
and see something very camp.

1077
00:50:41,480 --> 00:50:43,680
But, actually, I saw myself on
the stage.

1078
00:50:43,680 --> 00:50:47,600
We've all seen each other
on this stage via your story.

1079
00:50:47,600 --> 00:50:52,200
I can still feel this emotion.
It was so powerful.

1080
00:50:52,200 --> 00:50:55,480
I could see the fear in your
eyes,
and I could actually feel it.

1081
00:50:55,480 --> 00:50:57,800
When you changed and suddenly
blossomed,

1082
00:50:57,800 --> 00:51:00,000
a solar energy emerged

1083
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:01,800
and freed itself from all of
you.

1084
00:51:01,800 --> 00:51:05,320
My heart opened up all at once.
Thank you,

1085
00:51:05,320 --> 00:51:06,920
and congratulations on your
performance.

1086
00:51:06,920 --> 00:51:09,160
Thank you, Juliette.
It was very important for me to
do

1087
00:51:09,160 --> 00:51:12,280
what I did today,
because I was telling a Rusical,

1088
00:51:12,280 --> 00:51:15,480
but I was also telling my own
story.
They trusted me...

1089
00:51:15,720 --> 00:51:17,440
[sighs]

1090
00:51:17,960 --> 00:51:19,640
...to tell this story.

1091
00:51:21,960 --> 00:51:27,920
If I'm going to shine,
I can't do it without them.
There.

1092
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:29,440
Thank you.

1093
00:51:30,080 --> 00:51:32,640
Once again, well done!

1094
00:51:34,720 --> 00:51:36,040
Let's get on with it.

1095
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:38,240
Punani.

1096
00:51:38,240 --> 00:51:39,280
[laughs]

1097
00:51:39,280 --> 00:51:41,160
Can you make this outfit in a
larger size?

1098
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:44,640
Because I really need
this outfit for myself.

1099
00:51:44,960 --> 00:51:46,000
No worries.

1100
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:47,040
About your performance,

1101
00:51:47,040 --> 00:51:49,880
as Dragoye and Dragoya, you were
awesome.

1102
00:51:49,880 --> 00:51:51,920
It made me very happy.

1103
00:51:51,920 --> 00:51:55,680
"When We Arrive as Queens"
is a fucking hit song.

1104
00:51:55,680 --> 00:51:56,760
[laughs]

1105
00:51:56,760 --> 00:52:00,320
An amazing hit song.
That was great, bravo.

1106
00:52:00,320 --> 00:52:02,360
You looked great.

1107
00:52:02,360 --> 00:52:05,240
If I need to look at details,

1108
00:52:05,240 --> 00:52:07,760
one shone slightly brighter
than the other.

1109
00:52:08,680 --> 00:52:12,000
But thanks for your energy
and for bringing the elements

1110
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:14,440
to make the story evolve.
Well done to both of you.

1111
00:52:14,440 --> 00:52:15,440
Thank you.

1112
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:19,760
-Ginger Bitch.
-Good evening, little bitches.

1113
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:23,520
Fasten your seat belts.
Ginger Bitch is fully strapped
in.

1114
00:52:23,520 --> 00:52:26,440
Indeed, it's extremely well
done.

1115
00:52:26,440 --> 00:52:30,280
The corset is, of course, a
tribute
to Jean-Paul Gaultier.

1116
00:52:30,280 --> 00:52:33,440
The braids are amazing.
Everything is...

1117
00:52:33,440 --> 00:52:36,080
-You set off fantasies.
-I love your look.

1118
00:52:36,080 --> 00:52:41,120
And it's true, it makes me kind
of wet.

1119
00:52:41,120 --> 00:52:43,880
I love the name Esmerldwa.

1120
00:52:43,880 --> 00:52:45,000
[laughs]

1121
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:47,080
You didn't have many lines,
when you arrived onstage,

1122
00:52:47,080 --> 00:52:50,640
all eyes were on you,
and you really were into it.

1123
00:52:50,640 --> 00:52:52,280
Don't forget to change your
make-up too.

1124
00:52:52,760 --> 00:52:56,720
Esmeraldwa had the same evil
look,

1125
00:52:56,720 --> 00:52:58,840
and I struggled to connect with
your eyes,

1126
00:52:58,840 --> 00:53:02,160
and to see the energy
you were trying to convey.

1127
00:53:02,880 --> 00:53:03,960
Okay.

1128
00:53:04,880 --> 00:53:06,640
Moon!

1129
00:53:06,640 --> 00:53:07,840
Hi.

1130
00:53:08,360 --> 00:53:14,400
In the Rusical,
your character was the best
played.

1131
00:53:14,400 --> 00:53:17,000
You embodied it really well
with a lot of humor,

1132
00:53:17,240 --> 00:53:19,760
and I also enjoyed the quality

1133
00:53:19,760 --> 00:53:21,480
of the transformation of your
face.

1134
00:53:21,720 --> 00:53:24,160
It's incredibly brave.

1135
00:53:24,160 --> 00:53:29,400
It must have been quite painful
to play a toxic parent,

1136
00:53:29,400 --> 00:53:33,240
because, unfortunately,
it's very common in the
community

1137
00:53:33,800 --> 00:53:35,640
to face this kind of person,

1138
00:53:36,080 --> 00:53:38,640
and you embodied him
wonderfully.

1139
00:53:38,640 --> 00:53:41,160
Thank you for putting yourself
at risk. It paid off.

1140
00:53:41,160 --> 00:53:42,200
Thanks a lot.

1141
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:44,320
Mami Watta!

1142
00:53:44,560 --> 00:53:45,960
I love this look.

1143
00:53:45,960 --> 00:53:49,760
It reminds me a lot of
the creations of Balmain,

1144
00:53:49,760 --> 00:53:51,840
the silhouettes of the Saharan
people.

1145
00:53:51,840 --> 00:53:54,240
Grace Jones in Alaïa has nothing
on you.

1146
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:57,240
It's just as pretty
as what you did onstage.

1147
00:53:57,240 --> 00:54:00,400
I understand that musical comedy
was a dream of yours.

1148
00:54:00,400 --> 00:54:03,160
-Yeah.
-If you came here

1149
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:05,040
thinking you were going
to be a fashion queen,

1150
00:54:05,040 --> 00:54:07,280
to me, you will remain a baker
forever,

1151
00:54:07,280 --> 00:54:11,440
because you sold it very well!

1152
00:54:11,440 --> 00:54:14,560
The Baker was just phenomenal.

1153
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:17,800
She stole the scene every time
she opened her mouth.

1154
00:54:17,800 --> 00:54:21,640
You were the light.
You shone on everyone.

1155
00:54:21,640 --> 00:54:25,160
It was great to see and to feel.

1156
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:27,640
If I had a baker like that...

1157
00:54:28,000 --> 00:54:29,160
[laughs]

1158
00:54:29,160 --> 00:54:32,240
...I'd go refine my brioche more
often.

1159
00:54:32,240 --> 00:54:34,040
[laughs]

1160
00:54:34,040 --> 00:54:37,400
-That's it.
-Thank you.

1161
00:54:38,920 --> 00:54:41,640
Thanks, girls, go unpack your
jewelry

1162
00:54:41,640 --> 00:54:43,200
while we deliberate.

1163
00:54:43,200 --> 00:54:45,040
-Thanks.
-Thank you.

1164
00:54:45,040 --> 00:54:46,840
[applause]

1165
00:54:46,840 --> 00:54:47,840
Let's go.

1166
00:54:49,320 --> 00:54:55,400
[upbeat music]

1167
00:54:55,880 --> 00:54:57,960
How are you, girls?

1168
00:54:57,960 --> 00:55:00,560
-I'm fine.
-It's ambivalent.

1169
00:55:00,560 --> 00:55:01,640
It's very complicated.

1170
00:55:01,640 --> 00:55:03,680
Everyone got positive reviews.

1171
00:55:03,680 --> 00:55:05,480
What will they decide?

1172
00:55:05,480 --> 00:55:06,520
No idea.

1173
00:55:06,520 --> 00:55:08,360
Who will be on the top and on
the bottom?

1174
00:55:08,360 --> 00:55:11,640
No part was below the others.

1175
00:55:11,640 --> 00:55:13,160
-Exactly.
-And that's great.

1176
00:55:13,160 --> 00:55:14,720
Everyone shone.

1177
00:55:14,720 --> 00:55:16,400
I don't feel that way at all.

1178
00:55:16,400 --> 00:55:17,640
Oh, shit!

1179
00:55:17,920 --> 00:55:20,400
This part was forced upon me.

1180
00:55:20,400 --> 00:55:22,760
I tried to get another part.

1181
00:55:22,760 --> 00:55:25,200
Nobody listened to me, apart
from Keiona.

1182
00:55:25,200 --> 00:55:29,000
I can't let them say
that life is beautiful

1183
00:55:29,000 --> 00:55:30,400
and that everyone played a role

1184
00:55:30,400 --> 00:55:32,360
and got the part they wanted.

1185
00:55:32,360 --> 00:55:35,320
It really pissed me off
that when I tried to plead my
case

1186
00:55:35,320 --> 00:55:38,280
and get another part,
you didn't hesitate to say,

1187
00:55:38,280 --> 00:55:40,440
"No, you're not right for this
part."

1188
00:55:40,440 --> 00:55:42,040
-Who?
-Cookie, for example.

1189
00:55:42,040 --> 00:55:43,680
"You're not right for the duet.

1190
00:55:43,680 --> 00:55:45,600
Punani is a better fit.
You should do that."

1191
00:55:45,600 --> 00:55:46,600
Excuse me?

1192
00:55:46,600 --> 00:55:49,480
I wanted a specific part
and was fighting to get it.

1193
00:55:49,480 --> 00:55:51,000
Nobody has a say in the matter.

1194
00:55:51,000 --> 00:55:53,960
In the end, I got the part
nobody wanted.

1195
00:55:53,960 --> 00:55:56,360
The part that didn't have many
lines.

1196
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:59,080
As far as I'm concerned,
I've been robbed of my
challenge.

1197
00:56:00,680 --> 00:56:02,480
Drama!

1198
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:05,440
I don't understand
why you're saying this now.

1199
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:08,640
You feel that your performance
wasn't up to scratch,

1200
00:56:08,640 --> 00:56:10,920
so, now, you decide to say you
were robbed.

1201
00:56:10,920 --> 00:56:12,560
It's hypocritical.

1202
00:56:13,200 --> 00:56:15,400
It's going downhill!
[laughs]

1203
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:18,120
You felt this way yesterday,
but you didn't say anything?

1204
00:56:18,120 --> 00:56:20,560
It's not hypocritical at all,
Cookie.
I said it yesterday.

1205
00:56:20,560 --> 00:56:22,720
You didn't listen,
because you were in your
thing...

1206
00:56:22,720 --> 00:56:24,000
It wasn't up to me to decide.

1207
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:25,480
But those next to me

1208
00:56:25,480 --> 00:56:27,640
heard it wasn't the part I'd
chosen.

1209
00:56:27,640 --> 00:56:29,040
You're entitled to feel that
way.

1210
00:56:29,040 --> 00:56:30,640
-Of course.
-But I don't understand

1211
00:56:30,640 --> 00:56:32,640
how it's my fault.

1212
00:56:32,640 --> 00:56:34,800
She chose a part, she's a big
girl.

1213
00:56:34,800 --> 00:56:36,760
She can defend herself.

1214
00:56:36,760 --> 00:56:39,120
I didn't say it's your fault.

1215
00:56:39,120 --> 00:56:40,840
So, why are you mentioning me?

1216
00:56:40,840 --> 00:56:42,760
-Well...
-You're a big girl.

1217
00:56:42,760 --> 00:56:46,160
You can fight your battle on
your own.

1218
00:56:46,160 --> 00:56:47,800
Don't pin this on me.

1219
00:56:49,240 --> 00:56:51,640
It's even better
than The Young and the Restless.

1220
00:56:52,240 --> 00:56:56,640
"No! I can't let you say that,
Samantha."

1221
00:56:56,640 --> 00:57:00,120
You were great as Emeraldwa.
It was hilarious.

1222
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:02,720
Nobody would have danced like
this.

1223
00:57:02,720 --> 00:57:04,800
And, uh... [laughs]

1224
00:57:04,800 --> 00:57:06,760
Keiona is trying her best

1225
00:57:06,760 --> 00:57:08,640
to calm things down. I say, "No!

1226
00:57:08,640 --> 00:57:10,440
Honey, let them fight!"

1227
00:57:10,440 --> 00:57:13,320
I say, "Fire, fire, fire, keep
going!"

1228
00:57:13,320 --> 00:57:15,080
Once again, maybe it's my fault.

1229
00:57:15,080 --> 00:57:18,240
I want what's best for the
group,
and I'm always trying to help.

1230
00:57:18,640 --> 00:57:20,400
It's okay, I won't do it again.

1231
00:57:20,400 --> 00:57:27,200
[sings] And so, on this note...
[all vocalizing]

1232
00:57:29,120 --> 00:57:34,360
[sings] Let's go back onstage.

1233
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:40,360
Okay, ladies, it's time to chat.

1234
00:57:40,960 --> 00:57:42,520
What do you think of my queens?

1235
00:57:42,520 --> 00:57:44,480
Let's start with Cookie.

1236
00:57:44,480 --> 00:57:46,520
Cookie was great tonight.

1237
00:57:46,520 --> 00:57:48,640
Her look on the runway

1238
00:57:48,640 --> 00:57:52,960
is a truly glamorous Hollywood
look.

1239
00:57:52,960 --> 00:57:54,480
Who wouldn't want to wear this?

1240
00:57:54,480 --> 00:57:55,680
Sara Forever.

1241
00:57:55,960 --> 00:57:57,800
I loved it.

1242
00:57:58,040 --> 00:58:02,440
This kids sewing club aspect is
very '80s.

1243
00:58:02,440 --> 00:58:06,640
Since the start of the
competition,
she's surprised us every time.

1244
00:58:06,640 --> 00:58:10,000
Keiona! Quasimollo.

1245
00:58:10,000 --> 00:58:11,160
[applause]

1246
00:58:11,160 --> 00:58:12,760
-Oh, yeah.
-That was...

1247
00:58:12,760 --> 00:58:14,640
I can't stop clapping.

1248
00:58:14,640 --> 00:58:18,320
I couldn't stop crying, like
everyone.

1249
00:58:18,320 --> 00:58:22,360
Punani! Sara is still the
dominant twin.

1250
00:58:22,360 --> 00:58:24,240
Her performance was great.

1251
00:58:24,240 --> 00:58:25,960
She's very professional

1252
00:58:25,960 --> 00:58:29,960
and knows how to work in pairs.
Her look was very nice today.

1253
00:58:29,960 --> 00:58:32,640
But she was slightly below the
others.

1254
00:58:32,880 --> 00:58:34,480
Ginger Bitch.

1255
00:58:34,480 --> 00:58:36,440
-Oh, my.
-I have to say

1256
00:58:36,440 --> 00:58:38,600
that I really loved her look.

1257
00:58:38,600 --> 00:58:40,800
But in the Rusical,

1258
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:42,280
she was below the others.

1259
00:58:42,280 --> 00:58:44,480
The challenge is greater
when you have a small part.

1260
00:58:44,480 --> 00:58:46,360
In Season 12, I had a small part
too.

1261
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:50,480
In a musical, you need to act,
even if you don't have lines.

1262
00:58:50,840 --> 00:58:54,640
It's a shame she didn't take
the opportunity to shine,

1263
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:56,440
even when the spotlight wasn't
on her.

1264
00:58:56,440 --> 00:58:57,480
Yeah.

1265
00:58:57,480 --> 00:59:01,280
Moon. It was crazy tonight.

1266
00:59:01,280 --> 00:59:03,400
Yeah, that makeup was...

1267
00:59:03,400 --> 00:59:04,800
She managed

1268
00:59:04,800 --> 00:59:07,680
to make us smile, despite her
cruel part.

1269
00:59:07,680 --> 00:59:09,640
But, on the runway,
I didn't like her outfit.

1270
00:59:09,640 --> 00:59:11,640
She's got us used to better than
that.

1271
00:59:11,640 --> 00:59:13,040
Mami Watta.

1272
00:59:13,040 --> 00:59:15,560
She's getting better every week.

1273
00:59:15,560 --> 00:59:19,560
And she still has many things to
give us.

1274
00:59:19,560 --> 00:59:22,000
If she wasn't here,

1275
00:59:22,000 --> 00:59:23,920
but on a real musical, I would
buy it.

1276
00:59:23,920 --> 00:59:25,720
Yes, at one point...

1277
00:59:25,720 --> 00:59:27,320
No, come on, everyone...

1278
00:59:27,320 --> 00:59:33,600
[indistinct chatter]

1279
00:59:34,600 --> 00:59:35,640
Quiet!

